None, 'body': 'From the Document

> https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/dashboard/commit-a-product-submission
I'm trying to Commit a product submission by 

> https://manage.devcenter.microsoft.com/v2.0/my/hardware/products/{productID}/submissions/{submissionID}/commit
it returns a null response,status code = 202,I think it works.
But when I'm trying to get the status of the submission
> https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/dashboard/get-a-submission
It returns
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38720296/160782348-0b2f880a-8576-4f77-9527-3b9926bbd6df.png)
and the web page shows
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38720296/160782818-b787b525-b4f4-4aae-b539-a6648eea20bb.png)
How can I commit a submission Successfully？
----------------------------------------------------
Update on 2022/03/31
Now I can Commit successfully.
Seems like when you create a new product, the Value of _requestedSignatures_  can only be selected from the following list
"requestedSignatures": [
    "WINDOWS_v100_TH2_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS1_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS2_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS3_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS4_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS5_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_19H1_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_VB_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_TH2_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS1_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS2_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS3_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS4_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS5_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_19H1_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_VB_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_CO_FULL"
  ]
But if you selected a value like
"requestedSignatures": [
    "WINDOWS_v100_TH2_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS1_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS2_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS3_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS4_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_RS5_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_19H1_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_VB_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_TH2_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS1_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS2_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS3_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS4_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_RS5_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_19H1_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_VB_FULL",
    "WINDOWS_v100_X64_CO_FULL",
    **"WINDOWS_v100_SERVER_X64_TH2_FULL"**(this value is not on the list)
]
The Commit will going Fail 
[Enter feedback here]

Thanks for reaching out to our team. This particular mechanism is monitored by the men and women who write the driver documentation posted on doc.microsoft.com. Unfortunately, we don’t have the resources to help troubleshoot driver development issues sent our way.  
 
Your best bet is to use one or both of the two really good forums where other driver developers and Microsoft engineers can be found. The first is [Microsoft Q&A](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/answers/products/). The other is the [OSR NTDEV forum](https://community.osr.com/categories/ntdev). You can post your question there, and like-minded developers usually give feedback fairly quickly. 

I'm glad you received an answer from Viktor with Microsoft’s Developer Support Center. You could also follow up with them.
 
Again, thanks for reaching out. Best of luck with this issue.

 ~ *Mark*

Your best bet is to use one or both of the two really good forums where other driver developers and Microsoft engineers can be found. The first is [Microsoft Q&A](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/answers/products/). The other is the [OSR NTDEV forum](https://community.osr.com/categories/ntdev). You can post your question there, and like-minded developers usually give feedback fairly quickly. 
 
Again, thanks for reaching out. Best of luck with this issue.
